This file contains all the regions in Emberland.


In Emberland there is a region called Riverbank Retreat and it's description is: A small tourist place located north-west side of the map. Here people would come to the famous hotel, build near the lake, to enjoy the beautiful scenes viewed from it. But unfortunately now the hotel which was never closed is abandoned and instead of people you will find zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Nelson's Lumberyard and it's description is: A known place, where timber and other building materials were stored and sold, located south side of the map. It was owned by Nelson (Father of Maynard and Meeker) and was one of the busiest place where many people worked there but now it's just an abandoned yard. You will only find zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee instead of workers and timber scattered on the ground. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Red Pine Ranch and it's description is: A large farm located south-west side of the map. It was mainly for breeding and raising of cattle, sheep, or horses. Many animals were kept but now it has none as there was no one left to look after them. You will only find zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee and empty stables. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Maynard Loggers and it's description is: A known place, where wood was converted into timber, located west side of the map. These timber were then send to Nelson's Lumberyard in order to sell them. It was owned by Maynard (Brother of Meeker) and was one of the busiest place where many people worked there but now it's just an abandoned place. You will only find zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee instead of workers and timber scattered on the ground. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Meekers Mill and it's description is: A known place, where wood was converted into timber, located centre of the map. These timber were then send to Nelson's Lumberyard in order to sell them. It was owned by Meekers (Brother of Maynard) and was one of the busiest place where many people worked there but now it's just an abandoned place. You will only find zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee instead of workers and timber scattered on the ground. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Cloudsville and it's description is: A small town located north side of the map. It was a peaceful place where the villagers lived joyfully. Now it has became a miserable place filled with violent zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Point Slope and it's description is: A small town, build on a high mountain, located south-east side of the map. Very few families lived there due to very cold temperature and its location. It is very difficult to reach it and is fully covered with snow.Though there were few people living in it now no one is left except zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Alpine Mine and it's description is: A small mine in the snow located centre of the map. The place is known to be rich in rocks and minerals. But now it's just an abandoned mine full of stone blocks which were left by the miners in hurry and zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Littleton and it's description is: A small civilization build in desert located north-east side of the map. It contains mud houses since the mud walls in these houses keep them cooler inside even in such hot climatic regions and help people live comfortably in hot temperatures. But these houses are now abandoned and you will only find zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee in them. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called Sandy Plains and it's description is: A small town build in desert located north-east side of the map. It is very close to the sea but the villagers had to walk miles from their house for drinking water. Even though the temperature was very hot out there and there was scarcity of drinking water, people lived there. But now no one is left except zombies like normies, troopers, nursers, red bellies, pukers and especially Banshee in them. It is a tier I ruin which contains a green card, yellow card and green vault.

In Emberland there is a region called River City and it's description is: A densely populated city located north-west side of the map. People would come here from far away to visit the Church. Now it's just an abandoned city with zombies and The Church is taken by the armed villians where yellow vault is located and many loots are stored. It is a tier II ruin so be more caution as you will find two Banshees instead of one and a new boss Vulture ready with his gun.

In Emberland there is a region called Silver City and it's description is: located south-east side of the map.

In Emberland there is a region called Port Harlow and it's description is: A densely populated city located east side of the map.. People would come here from far away to visit the Church. Now it's just an abandoned city with zombies and The Church is taken by the armed villians where yellow vault is located and many loots are stored. It is a tier II ruin so be more caution as you will find two Banshees instead of one and a new boss Vulture ready with his gun.

In Emberland there is a region called Mt. Bedford and it's description is: A densely populated city located south-east side of the map.. People would come here from far away to visit the Church. Now it's just an abandoned city with zombies and The Church is taken by the armed villians where yellow vault is located and many loots are stored. It is a tier II ruin so be more caution as you will find two Banshees instead of one and a new boss Vulture ready with his gun.

In Emberland there is a region called Port Tackson and it's description is: Red vault lab

7eb89e12-ff8e-41d5-a382-3c1b0f27ccf2.text: Mission EVO is the first mobile survival game developed with Unreal Engine 5. It will be released in 2023. THE WORLD HAS BEEN RUINED. RAID FOR EMBERS, FIGHT FOR SURVIVAL! In this open world known as Emberland, the only aim is to survive... till the very end. Danger lurks around every corner, everything wants you dead. You have to survive through the cruelest of competition - not only against all kinds of mutant creatures, but against hundreds of other desperate players. Keep in mind, by hook or by crook, everything goes! But being alive is always the aim of the game. The light of Ember is guiding your way. Embark on this fantastic journey, NOW!

This file contains all the NPCs in Emberland.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Dozer they are Armed Villians that can be found in tier II ruins. They normally guard the yellow vaults with thier armoured skin which are made of ruin particals. They also have machine guns for their defence which continuously fire bullet and can make player's body full with holes. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.30.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Panzer they are Armed Villians that can be found in Port Tackson. They normally guard the red vault with thier armoured skin which are made of ruin particals. They also have machine guns for their defence which continuously fire bullet and can make player's body full with holes. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.45.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Scoper they are Long-range attacking armed villians with snipers to defend yellow vaults. Don't approach them without any armor since they can one-shot you. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them. Veteran players leave them be since they can warn them from potential competitors while accessing yellow vault.Spawns at lvl.30.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Elite Scoper they are Advanced Long range attacking armed villians with snipers to defend red vault. Don't approach them without any armor since they can one-shot you. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them.Spawns at lvl.45.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Sentinel Drone they are Mini auto-aim drones spawned by the scientist boss KANE in the Highly dangerous PORT TACKSON. They damage the players and distract them  to prevent them from attacking KANE. They are not so damaging for High lvl players but killing them son is advised. Do not drop any materials when defeated.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Gunner Drone they are Mini auto-aim drones spawned by the scientist boss KANE in the Highly dangerous PORT TACKSON. They damage the players and distract them  to prevent them from attacking KANE. They are not so damaging for High lvl players but killing them son is advised. Do not drop any materials when defeated.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Normie/Normies they are Low level Zombified humanoids found in all types of ruins except Port Tackson. They can be easily defeated, but in a group they can even kill you. Making good use of triggers and traps can make exploration and combat easier. For example, destroying a propane tank will set off a large explosion, dealing damage to nearby zombies. Spawns at lvl.5.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Trooper/Troopers they are Slightly high level Zombified humanoids found in all types of ruins except Port Tackson. They have high defensive capacities. They are slow due to their heavy armor but one stroke deals a great damage so be careful. Spawns at lvl.10.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Nurser/Nursers they are Slightly high level Zombified humanoids found in all types of ruins except Port Tackson. They boast great speed, so make sure to defeat them quickly. Spawns at lvl.10.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Red Belly/Red Bellies they are Special Zombified humanoid found in all types of ruins except Port Tackson. They will explode and deal massive damage when someone gets near. Try to steer clear of them. Highly dangerous even for veterans, be advised to kill them first when you see them (Shoot at Sight). Spawns at lvl.10.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Puker/Pukers they are Special Zombified humanoid found in all types of ruin except Port Tackson. They deal damage to players by spewing acid from a distance. Keep an eye out for their sneak attacks. Highly irritating, be advised to kill them first when you see them (Shoot at Sight). Spawn at lvl.10.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Banshee/Banshees they are Banshees move extremely fast (even teleport) and have very high HP. They can shriek to deal massive Damage from a distance. Once defeated, Banshees will drop Embers and numerous supplies. Fight them with caution.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Mobber/Mobbers they are Middle range attacking armed villians with MPX to defend yellow vaults. They can approach the player quickly, so be very careful. By increasing your character level, you can deal more damage to them and reduce the damage you take. You should take cover and use middle-range weapons (PPSH-41, AKM, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.25.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Rager/Ragers they are Advance middle-range attacking armed villians with vector to defend red vault. They can approach the player quickly, so be very careful. By increasing your character level, you can deal more damage to them and reduce the damage you take. You should take cover and use middle-range weapons (PPSH-41, AKM, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.40.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Mob Captain/Mob Captains they are Middle-range attacking armed villians with M4A1 to defend yellow vaults. They can approach the player quickly, so be very careful. By increasing your character level, you can deal more damage to them and reduce the damage you take. You should take cover and use middle-range weapons (PPSH-41, AKM, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.30.

In Emberland there are NPCs named Rage Captain/Rage Captains they are Advance middle-range attacking armed villians with AUG to defend red vault. They can approach the player quickly, so be very careful. By increasing your character level, you can deal more damage to them and reduce the damage you take. You should take cover and use middle-range weapons (PPSH-41, AKM, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.45.

In Emberland there is a NPC named Kane they are Kane also known as the mad scientist shoots beams of laser which can penetrate through objects and damage you from a distance. He has a very high HP and can also heal itself. He also launches drones which attacks you and distracts from him. Once defeated, he will drop Embers and very rare supplies. Fight with caution as he is one of most powerful bosses in Emberland.

In Emberland there is a NPC named Zed they are Armed Villians that can be found in Port Tackson. They normally guard the red vault with thier armoured skin which are made of ruin particals. They also have machine guns for their defence which continuously fire bullet and can make player's body full with holes. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.45.(Not confirmed)

In Emberland there is a NPC named Sicario they are Advance middle-range attacking armed villians with AUG to defend red vault. They can approach the player quickly, so be very careful. By increasing your character level, you can deal more damage to them and reduce the damage you take. You should take cover and use middle-range weapons (PPSH-41, AKM, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.45.(Not confirmed)

In Emberland there is a NPC named Goyle they are Armed Villians that can be found in Port Tackson. They normally guard the red vault with thier armoured skin which are made of ruin particals. They also have machine guns for their defence which continuously fire bullet and can make player's body full with holes. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them. Spawns at lvl.45.(Not confirmed)

In Emberland there is a NPC named Mammon they are Advanced Long range attacking armed villians with snipers to defend red vault. Don't approach them without any armor since they can one-shot you. You should take cover and use long-range weapons (Bows and Arrows, Snippers, etc) to defeat them.Spawns at lvl.45.(Not confirmed)

In Emberland there is a NPC named Vulture they are Vulture, a genius-caliber talent for invention, can kill you in 4 different ways. He carries 2 different weapons for his defense and has very high HP which also gets healed by itself after when he receives some damage. He has a shotgun which deals great damage at short distance and a killing machine which can fire deadly missiles and rockets at a great distance and which can also function as a flamethrower that penetrates through walls and damages you. Once defeated, he will drop Embers and numerous supplies. Fight them with caution as he has one of the most dangerous weapon in Emberland.
